[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering class path issues**\n\nI’m thinking about a potential issue with the new finalizer class path, related to the package com_google_inject.guice and its inner class. It looks like there’s an InnerClasses attribute for the outer class — specifically, it will be called DecoupledFinalizer$ShutDown. That's good to note! I’m also aware there's a potential issue with a custom helper class in this package that has an underscore, which ties into legal considerations.\n\n**Considering class loading issues**\n\nI'm thinking about structuring how to handle URLClassLoader and Class.forName. It seems like trying to instantiate these might trigger an unsupported error before class resources are ready. Our writeDecoupledFinalizerClass reads resources first, so maybe that's why native fails before dynamic loading. I’m wondering if we could move an unsupported probe before reading? Also, using base64 for class bytes seems hard to manage due to size. Maybe I should try defining a small generated class in a throwaway ClassLoader instead!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0546e149f87d035b0169fa4de10d088196a7c0117d793983b3\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-k337Hc3on-Dcygh2lBXRZPf1GuQE3tG23ZOjbM_loEF4H66LV-w7cPqNrcsriR-fzV579JgPoAiK_6XBzRIhHJcQvq_wvzZ8Q0lPyNCt1J2iaGD9aj5m2cEkR5dHtDyTnGoyk1hY2t1TY0ZmwMhmWVM83qjC7Jim08mEszCY73sTgv7MX-GPYLZpgcDd794I4AlUrwvScNLFmU1HuoHBaN9xfLtguZF86HkOaEeji8v4FmybkZLpL-mtkA7XKfQ1MeXFKF_g0pow5oVsjq0Gz53XqSF1aBao3X3vb-deFVaOUV6eEW9-vdEP39IXg-D5GwdGny5ZG9sbwi4WPijW6vM0RZZsAz32CuSdcLixETCnTJTXn_DCD-nuhcmDB5ZPz7Lo0y45zUelwoWfTVNpyOLH54TEi59CAawbb1Zqfh5EAr4knxx6WKlz3h7S0T820-2JpzUf_QEiunWtfVzPK5mg5EIP_YKKYgiKSOo9vw-X3DqGaMk3fBnIQV0IrCwK-pz7Y9mrt_xvr5J0jqGucqvGJAw9pi5grG-elxZe4pMbOSzDduIa3EMeBrNwMZ0TkYfl4mn9iTVzgYOoujA0xo5g2N-7eq-5-t-VTd8XLrpuk1fjUp1omuoJ7_HHn78HcdVk-1SXdxV39ZlxdqV23ogB6bJW0s7-770ZGd1li390zgk6qXyki0OJ2B