F/native-image, which is interesting. However, I want to make sure I don’t broaden the scope beyond what's necessary. My next step is to check the untracked status of these src/test/resources files carefully.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_LnMpy1kKFFsh6Veaer4Cikfo|fc_0546e149f87d035b0169fa4eb6e9d4819698f052db62fe4e47", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/src/test/resources -maxdepth 5 -type f -print -exec sh -c 'echo --- $1; head -20 \"$1\"' sh {} \\; || true && git status --short tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2280, "output": 3126, "cacheRead": 33280, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38686, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778011781958, "responseId": "resp_0546e149f87d035b0169fa4e8694648196952ddbbaae8bd75e"}}
