on check would be required. I also want to recall the function `needsClassLoaderPermissionCheck(from, to)`, which returns true if the two are different and one isn't an ancestor of the other.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class loading**\\n\\nI need to think about using `ClassLoader.getPlatformClassLoader()`, but if a SecurityManager is installed, it could complicate things. If a child is created before the SecurityManager, it might affect the process. This setup also makes the system loader check for any denied permissions. I really want to ensure I’m considering all angles here to get it right!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_t4cu9J1tLQ8ShGE36bJpvGKK|fc_0546e149f87d035b0169fa4f2c1ff0819698943db59e6d25e7", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/src/test/java/com_google_inject/guice/FinalizableReferenceQueueInnerDecoupledLoaderTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "        ChildFirstGuiceJarLoader(URL[] urls) {\n            super(urls, $FinalizableReferenceQueue.class.getClassLoader());\n        }\n", "newText": "        ChildFirstGuiceJarLoader(URL[] urls) {\n            super(urls, ClassLoader.getPlatformClassLoader());\n        }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1719, "output": 1162, "cacheRead": 49664, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 52545, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778011929807, "responseId": "resp_0546e149f87d035b0169fa4f1b94dc81969228badf2e14331d"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_t4cu9J1tLQ8ShGE36bJpvGKK|fc_0546e149f87d035b0169fa4f2c1ff0819698943db59e6d25e7", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/src/test/java/com_google_inject/guice/FinalizableReferenceQueueInnerDecoupledLoaderTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "     ...