e others. I wonder if XML timestamps play a role in this. I feel like I need to read more about other timestamps to clarify what's happening. There's definitely something worth exploring here regarding how the ordering works in JUnit.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Mokr0tcm6u1ACD9K7JGvWdcG|fc_0546e149f87d035b0169fa5056fa9c8196a635fe29e3726bd5", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "grep -H \"timestamp\" tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/build/test-results/test/TEST-*.xml", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 614, "output": 1340, "cacheRead": 54784, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 56738, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778012226653, "responseId": "resp_0546e149f87d035b0169fa5043f1308196bea87cc900c2933b"}}
