o issues. The DecoupledLoader should be loading the finalizer through URLClassLoader using the base URL. Now, I’m considering that the default parent for the URLClassLoader is the system classloader in Java 8, which plays into how the constructor for URLClassLoader operates with the URL array.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test initialization**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how our test uses a constructor, and that static initialization is occurring. I wonder if other tests might have loaded the FinalizableReferenceQueue (FRQ) earlier? The dynamic report seems to indicate that FRQ is covered from previous tests, possibly from MapMaker. If the FRQ was already initialized before the custom loader property, that could definitely impact our current test results. It's important to clarify this.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering native tests configuration**\\n\\nI'm thinking about native tests probably not using a custom system loader, and whether the system loader finds the finalizer. It looks like if the native includes a property, no catch is needed. I'm wondering if, under native with the system loader, ClassLoader.getSystemClassLoader().loadClass will work. I need to edit build.gradle, removing the security manager allowance and adding `jvmArgs '-Djava.system.class.loader=...'` for tests only. There’s a consideration of possible crashes due to the custom system loader, but it seems okay for now. I'll propose rewriting the test file.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_980v8aDsSfGBoziO9qZ42fiN|fc_0546e149f87d035b0169fa50f5001481968f9809fef7e8af58", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/src/test/java/com_google_inject/guice/InnerFinalizableReferenceQueueInnerDecoupledLoaderTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_google_inject.guice;\n\nimport com.google.inject.internal.util.$FinalizableReferenceQueue;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class InnerFinalizableReferenceQueueInnerDecoupledLoaderTest {\n    private static final String FINALIZER_CLASS_NAME = \"com.google.inject.internal.util.$Finalizer\";\n\n    @Test\n    void startsFinalizableReferenceQueueWithDecoupledFinalizerLoader() {\n        $FinalizableReferenceQueue queue = new $FinalizableReferenceQueue();\n\n        assertThat(queue).isNotNull();\n    }\n\n    public static final class DenyGuiceFinalizerSystemClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        public DenyGuiceFinalizerSystemClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\n            super(parent);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (isGuiceFinalizerClass(name)) {\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);\n            }\n            return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\n        }\n\n        private static boolean isGuiceFinalizerClass(String name) {\n            return name.equals(FINALIZER_CLASS_NAME) || name.startsWith(FINALIZER_CLASS_NAME + \"$\");\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 16668, "output": 3314, "cacheRead": 45056, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 65038, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778012363021, "responseId": "resp_0546e149f87d035b0169fa50cc37a4819680454457c9287a5e"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_980v8aDsSfGBoziO9qZ42fiN|fc_0546e149f87d035b0169fa50f5001481968f9809fef7e8af58", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1460 bytes to tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/src/test/java/com_google_inject/guic