d that the custom classloader’s parent is the built-in app. In Java 9, the app classloader isn’t a URL classloader either. This could lead to a potential issue where a dynamic access report from a Java agent might only track stack frames that the parent built-in loader manages, not the custom one. \\n\\nI wonder if we need a user-code filter modified from external sources without touching it. And should we remove any old files if remnants from a previous name linger? I'll need to check on that.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_bDVGmIdOJG8eJzygmaSg6OTK|fc_0546e149f87d035b0169fa51143420819683ba17d23bf965db", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/src/test/java/com_google_inject/guice -maxdepth 1 -type f -name '*Finalizable*' -print\npython3 - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfor f in ['tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/src/test/java/com_google_inject/guice/InnerFinalizableReferenceQueueInnerDecoupledLoaderTest.java','tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/build.gradle']:\n print('---', f)\n for i,l in enumerate(Path(f).read_text().splitlines(),1):\n  if len(l)>120:\n   print(i,len(l),l)\nPY\ngit status --short tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/src/test/java/com_google_inject/guice tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/build.gradle", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 618, "output": 704, "cacheRead": 66048, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 67370, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778012422852, "responseId": "resp_0546e149f87d035b0169fa510935b081968c668717b2ba2cfc"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_bDVGmIdOJG8eJzygmaSg6OTK|fc_0546e149f87d035b0169fa51143420819683ba17d23bf965db", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/src/test/java/com_google_inject/guice/InnerFinalizableReferen