[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring class loader options**\n\nI'm wondering about some alternatives, like using a separate helper in buildSrc, but that doesn't seem like the way. I could potentially set `java.system.class.loader` to a specific class in a JAR on the worker's classpath, but it looks like that won't be accessible. Maybe adding a test classes JAR to bootstrap could work, though I'm not so sure. It might be that Gradle's `Test` JVM command classpath is directly related to the test runtime classpath.\n\n**Considering class structure**\n\nI’m thinking maybe the current setup could fail, so I should create a separate top-level helper class with no external dependencies in its own file. I’ll also need to add test classes. This way, there won't be any issues with dynamic access mapping. I plan to use `DenyGuiceFinalizerSystemClassLoader.java`, making it public. Even though it adds another Java file that isn’t solely for dynamic testing, it helps keep things organized and straightforward.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0546e149f87d035b0169fa51192e28819686f619eb842c34bb\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-lEtCLnQ-cpjOQVQ8STngR2yO9Csszrm2Gl-ogphp_pbEV2YLvusfvvNe_Sq5Gw3EYdipkdERFquGr0MN9GmxMR45l0e2WYu9rqnwBubq5k8b3xw3Ji-UdhXBsxzLSWgIuApVe21SFNxOEv3JEiQXR5nh09aBKlmXZ60ZIs6kTUPLPGiqYM30bocaTCxRZWpouYaZT2vJHgw5HNVScrsaYJDh_RQp__Y6yDIADysXgHdkFeUooCoicXUimph-mbZl7GYXJWc1WdBNT2g8-7_nVv5bvZepbrmiwL_QKB57ry0rK_YxTC-4tfsu-FH7MmXH3LtPjdCbDC7vGsJUT1DNWw-OtU9Qfd7YBiz26RY2pH3ET1v7_LahB1vE5TSpGe1hcTdN3R44qHGMS_yOi5LQjN9Z3OvwxE9tjO1DbWpPTbnDBiiLFTfjLhbwkqc_q6KvyVP-gcdgO5a3t5aZj-UuMwE1GcxRGVTw0z6X1sOAamoT9GxHRwF_Of2ibGVSverFtGB-RmB-kModykRf2MXxpryLg-WQwUCcp0twbTi5OvX_h4pKCJpMcEuvwpbTtvD_Mv-qQCTdXS7u7OnsVtalYKoIRd5l906YSFXQ31WC2VAVHA2gMVh8oh0Ynb1Khwyo9S96AM-4UxYx8FsTgliRGCVfKrNeG8mFEuU8RoUPqDYNUfaKGET92bmfWh0fw8Fd7Pq_8OsZGV2i6NcrR1CLP10ucEpt_KJyOy2h_dibN2BRODhUs5vZsLR8l