t": "Fixed the failing test by removing the unsupported `SecurityManager` approach.\n\nWhat changed:\n\n- Replaced the `System.setSecurityManager(...)` based forcing mechanism with a custom system class loader.\n\n- Added helper class:\n  - `tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/src/test/java/com_google_inject/guice/DenyGuiceFinalizerSystemClassLoader.java`\n\n  This class loader refuses to load Guice’s `$Finalizer`, causing Guice’s `$FinalizableReferenceQueue$SystemLoader` path to fail naturally.\n\n- Simplified the dedicated active-class test:\n  - `tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/src/test/java/com_google_inject/guice/InnerFinalizableReferenceQueueInnerDecoupledLoaderTest.java`\n\n  It now just constructs `$FinalizableReferenceQueue`, which should force the fallback into `$FinalizableReferenceQueue$DecoupledLoader` under the JVM test setup.\n\n- Updated:\n  - `tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/build.gradle`\n\n  to package the helper class into a tiny bootclasspath jar and run JVM tests with:\n\n  - `-Djava.system.class.loader=com_google_inject.guice.DenyGuiceFinalizerSystemClassLoader`\n\nThis avoids `SecurityManager`, so it should no longer fail on Java versions where setting a security manager is unsupported. I did not run the tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0546e149f87d035b0169fa517d7cdc8196844f05744d4fb5fa\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 597, "output": 809, "cacheRead": 73216, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 74622, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778012529158, "responseId": "resp_0546e149f87d035b0169fa51723910819694099e1c1067f50d"}}
