4QPu7omu68Qt4iiwvRtzVR-etwiryUK6h_e7n2_kef64iOv4n_42R9pGqw3c8jStfM4HiuiKf1TUmesgzTbBsPkxNz0vHPCx9uWqlTalKmJhsWHCXIkEyNDTrkd-jYdGSYbBgbv_1hMB6mYiRGMatR-otwZAxl9d-O3smPYNHllVTzLBSrHnX_WXwzbUwmhilCwbJQVWXTYm0kq-4=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating JVM Argument Order**\\n\\nI’m considering whether to place doFirst jvmArgs after the test task starts. It seems this modifies JVM args before forking. However, I wonder if java.system.class.loader should come before bootclasspath. The order doesn’t matter much, except for the bootclasspath property, I think. There's a potential issue with a system classloader helper class being loaded from the boot jar, which only contains that class. Also, I’m wary of conflicts between custom and default class loaders, especially with split packages.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing ClassLoader Behavior**\\n\\nI'm considering how DirectLoader uses Class.forName to load Finalizer. It relies on the caller's defining loader, which could be the app's parent, not our custom loader. It can still load the Finalizer from the parent if Decoupled fails, although that shouldn't happen. There’s a possibility that different metadata might not include resource config for Finalizer. I think I might need an assertion to check that the system classloader helper is active, but it could fail in native execution.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Test Approach**\\n\\nI’m thinking that in the native environment, the test might only instantiate the queue, which simplifies things since there’s no NativeImageSupport. I should check the AGENTS, as they say not to run tests. The user mentioned an issue, and we fixed the setSecurityManager, so I'll provide an explanation. I believe it’s worth mentioning the custom system loader with the boot jar. I also need to consider removing any old untracked resources and ensuring user-code-filter modifications are clarified.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Fixed the failing test by removing the unsupported `SecurityManager` approach.\n\nWhat changed:\n\n- Replaced the `System.setSecurityManager(...)` based forcing mechanism with a custom system class loader.\n\n- Added helper class:\n  - `tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/src/test/java/com_google_inject/guice/DenyGuiceFinalizerSystemClassLoader.java`\n\n  This class loader refuses to load Guice’s `$Finalizer`, causing Guice’s `$FinalizableReferenceQueue$SystemLoader` path to fail naturally.\n\n- Simplified the dedicated active-class test:\n  - `tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/src/test/java/com_google_inject/guice/InnerFinalizableReferenceQueueInnerDecoupledLoaderTest.java`\n\n  It now just constructs `$FinalizableReferenceQueue`, which should force the fallback into `$FinalizableReferenceQueue$DecoupledLoader` under the JVM test setup.\n\n- Updated:\n  - `tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/build.gradle`\n\n  to package the helper class into a tiny bootclasspath jar and run JVM tests with:\n\n  - `-Djava.system.class.loader=com_google_inject.guice.DenyGuiceFinalizerSystemClassLoader`\n\nThis avoids `SecurityManager`, so it should no longer fail on Java versions where setting a security manager is unsupported. I did not run the tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0546e149f87d035b0169fa517d7cdc8196844f05744d4fb5fa\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 597, "output": 809, "cacheRead": 73216, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 74622, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778012529158, "responseId": "resp_0546e149f87d035b0169fa51723910819694099e1c1067f50d"}, "toolResults": []}
