but it seems the earlier issues were related to the bootclasspath. We decided to simplify things by separating them.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying Java test classes**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how to avoid generating extra Java files by using a nested class and implementing append. There’s something about the jvmArgs splitting, and I realized that the system class loader's naming convention includes a \\\"$\\\", while helper classes don’t have \\\"Test.\\\" It looks like I might not be generating a test correctly. However, putting helper classes into their own Java files might not violate the rule of keeping dynamic-access classes in dedicated test files. I prefer folding helpers into one test file as a nested public static class, though. Got it!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring nested class loading**\\n\\nI'm reflecting on the previous failure of the nested custom loader because it didn’t implement 'append.' I see that removing the Deny... file and rewriting tests with a nested URLClassLoader could work if I update the build.gradle to include the inner class, even with jvmArgs splitting. I'm also pondering the visibility of the class to the bootstrap. Should I load both the test class and inner class in the boot jar to be safe? But that might create duplicates in JUnit!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Addressing custom loader issues**\\n\\nIt might be okay, but I find it a bit strange. I realize that a custom system loader class can be top-level and not just for testing, allowing for one extra helper if necessary. A simpler fix could be editing the helper to extend URLClassLoader and implement the append method to prevent crashes. However, since the user wants a fix for the error, I must consider the potential dynamic coverage issue with Guice finalizer being loaded in the system class loader, which complicates things a bit.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_5UmvJitc81NUE5CWVrbhNeJU|fc_0546e149f87d035b0169fa51b2091481969332b639aa78d05a", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/src/test/java/com_google_inject/guice/DenyGuiceFinalizerSystemClassLoader.java", "offset": 1, "limit": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 24260, "output": 1201, "cacheRead": 61440, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 86901, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778012573742, "responseId": "resp_0546e149f87d035b0169fa519fda408196b592da8ec92bd786"}}
