he active test, as other tests may utilize $FinalizableReferenceQueue and the DecoupledLoader path. However, the system loader denies the finalizer for all tests, affecting coverage. \\n\\nThere seems to be a potential issue with native image runs, particularly since the system property in Gradle Test only applies there. While native image compile executes test classes, it doesn't use the Test tasks. I also have to consider dynamic class loading patterns and how the custom system loader interacts with native images. It’s good to know constructing $FinalizableReferenceQueue might still succeed now.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Fixed the JaCoCo crash caused by the custom system class loader.\n\nThe failure happened because JVM instrumentation requires a custom `java.system.class.loader` to define:\n\n```java\nappendToClassPathForInstrumentation(String path)\n```\n\nI updated:\n\n- `tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/src/test/java/com_google_inject/guice/DenyGuiceFinalizerSystemClassLoader.java`\n\nChanges:\n\n- It now extends `URLClassLoader` instead of plain `ClassLoader`.\n- It implements `appendToClassPathForInstrumentation(String path)` and adds the JaCoCo agent jar URL to itself.\n- It still denies only Guice’s `$Finalizer` class so `$FinalizableReferenceQueue$SystemLoader` falls through to `$FinalizableReferenceQueue$DecoupledLoader`.\n\nThis should resolve:\n\n```text\nSystem class loader does not define the appendToClassPathForInstrumentation method\n```\n\nI did not run the tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0546e149f87d035b0169fa51c8583c8196bfdbcd9b4b59860b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 834, "output": 610, "cacheRead": 87040, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 88484, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778012605241, "responseId": "resp_0546e149f87d035b0169fa51bec71881969d5281295f767fdc"}}
